# Disk Management in Linux

Disk management handles viewing disks, creating partitions, formatting, mounting, and controlling storage devices.  
This document explains **what disk management is**, **what it controls**, and **the essential commands**.

---

## 1. Management Area: Disk & Storage Management

---

## 2. Definition – What Disk Management Manages

Disk Management controls:

- Physical disks and partitions  
- File systems (ext4, xfs, etc.)  
- Mounting and unmounting drives  
- Disk usage monitoring  
- Logical Volume Management (LVM)  
- Swap memory  

It ensures proper storage configuration and system stability.

---

## 3. Commands List

---

### View Disks & Partitions

| Command | Used For |
|--------|-----------|
| `lsblk` | List block devices (disks/partitions) |
| `fdisk -l` | Show partition table |
| `blkid` | Show filesystem UUIDs |
| `df -h` | Check disk usage |
| `du -sh /path` | Check directory size |

---

### Partition Management

| Command | Used For |
|--------|-----------|
| `fdisk /dev/sdX` | Manage partitions (MBR) |
| `parted /dev/sdX` | Manage partitions (GPT) |

---

### Formatting Partitions

| Command | Used For |
|--------|-----------|
| `mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdX1` | Format as ext4 |
| `mkfs.xfs /dev/sdX1` | Format as XFS |

---

### Mounting & Unmounting

| Command | Used For |
|--------|-----------|
| `mount /dev/sdX1 /mnt` | Mount partition |
| `umount /mnt` | Unmount partition |
| `mount -o remount,rw /mnt` | Remount as read/write |

---

### LVM Management

| Command | Used For |
|--------|-----------|
| `pvcreate /dev/sdX` | Create physical volume |
| `vgcreate vg_name /dev/sdX` | Create volume group |
| `lvcreate -L 10G -n lv_name vg_name` | Create logical volume |
| `mkfs.ext4 /dev/vg_name/lv_name` | Format LV |
| `mount /dev/vg_name/lv_name /mnt` | Mount LV |

---

### Swap Management

| Command | Used For |
|--------|-----------|
| `mkswap /dev/sdX` | Create swap partition |
| `swapon /dev/sdX` | Enable swap |
| `swapoff /dev/sdX` | Disable swap |

---

## Summary

- Disk management includes partitioning, formatting, mounting, and monitoring.  
- LVM helps manage storage flexibly.  
- Swap improves memory performance.

